   562                                  ;
   563                                  ;       File Allocation Tables
   564                                  ;
   565                                  ;       The disk contains two copies of the File Allocation Table (FAT). On our disk, each FAT copy is 1200h bytes in
   566                                  ;       length. Each FAT entry contains the logical number of the next cluster. The first two entries are reserved. Our
   567                                  ;       OS.COM file here is 400h bytes in length. These 400h bytes contain familiar code that displays a message to the
   568                                  ;       screen. Our disk parameter table defines a cluster as containing one sector and each sector having 200h bytes.
   569                                  ;       Therefore, our FAT table must reserve only two clusters for OS.COM. The clusters used by OS.COM, then, will be
   570                                  ;       clusters 2 and 3. The entry value for cluster 3 is set to "0fffh" to indicate that it is the last cluster in the
   571                                  ;       chain.
   572                                  ;
   573                                  ;       Every three bytes encode two FAT entries as follows:
   574                                  ;
   575                                  ;       db      0abh,0cdh,0efh  ;even cluster: 0dabh, odd cluster: 0efch
   576                                  ;
   577                                  ;=======================================================================================================================
   578                                  ;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   579                                  ;
   580                                  ;       FAT copy 1                                                              @disk: 000200   @mem: n/a
   581                                  ;
   582                                  ;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
